cs.MS, cs.SC, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.SE

The paper discusses mathematical software systems, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.MS (Mathematical Software), which specifically deals with software for mathematical computation and reasoning. The paper also touches on aspects of software engineering (cs.SE) in terms of system interoperability and organization. The topics of inference and computation are relevant to cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), respectively. Finally, the aspect of concretization relates to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) in terms of generating and maintaining collections of mathematical objects.
